And then there were the embarrassing incidents for the franchise.
Forman, who was fired as general manager on the same day Paxson was reassigned, reportedly set up spies throughout the organization at one point.
Butler’s then-trainer, Travelle Gaines, once said he had met drug dealers with better morals than Forman.
Thibodeau was fired with a petulant press release.
A crowd at Navy Pier during All-Star Weekend in February 2020 hijacked a segment on ESPN with chants to “Fire GarPax."